benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/children - List children accounts

covered: Valid Request: Multiple success scenarios (default, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit levels, combinations) validate expected responses and fields.
Empty Response: TC07 and TC24 cover parent with no children and all children deleted returning empty arrays.
Query Parameters: Many combinations of valid query parameters and invalid parameter values are tested (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC16).
Authorization: Both unauthorized and forbidden cases are present (TC11, TC12).

Error Handling (client/server): Tests cover invalid accountId format (TC09), missing parent (TC10, TC08), dependency/service unavailable and timeout (TC14, TC18), and malformed input/injection (TC16, TC17).
Large Data / Performance: TC15 addresses large-volume retrieval and performance expectations.
Concurrency & Integration: Concurrent requests (TC21) and audit-service integration/consistency (TC22) are included.
Regression / Backward compatibility: Regression (TC19) and legacy client behavior (TC20) are covered.
Path-level errors: Missing accountId in path resulting in 404 is covered (TC25).
gaps: Pagination: No tests verify pagination behavior, limits, offsets, or server-side handling for large result sets (the large-volume test expects all 10,000 results but does not assert pagination).
Caching Behavior: No scenarios validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional GET behavior.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests for rate limiting or behavior under rapid repeated requests (429 scenarios are missing).
Response Schema Validation: While fields are asserted, there is no explicit test verifying full Account object schema compliance (types, required fields) or content-type/response headers beyond JSON.

Partial/Boundary Query Parameter Combinations: Although many combinations are present, edge cases like both boolean params true/false precedence and ambiguous combinations interactions are not exhaustively validated beyond a few rows in TC06.
Authorization scope testing: Tests cover 401/403 but lack fine-grained permission-scope checks (e.g., token with read-only vs admin scopes producing different results).
recommendations: Add pagination tests: verify limit/offset or page-size behavior, boundary values, and behavior when result count exceeds a single page. Include tests for clients requesting partial pages and ensure consistent total counts/next-links if applicable.
Add caching tests: assert presence and semantics of Cache-Control and ETag headers; include conditional GET (If-None-Match) to verify 304 responses.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate high request rates to confirm 429 responses or throttling behavior and proper Retry-After headers.
Add schema/contract validation tests: validate the full Account object schema (types, required properties) and response headers (Content-Type, charset).
Expand authorization tests: include tests for tokens with varying scopes/roles to confirm fine-grained access control behavior.

Clarify and expand query-param interaction tests: add explicit tests for precedence and combinations of accountWithBalance and accountWithBalanceAndCBA (e.g., both true/false and server-defined precedence) and for audit param defaulting/invalid enum values.
